 "MS:1002849", "name": "Search engine output file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/Zou_Rappsilber_JP_CPC_phospho_EDC.xlsx"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/Zou_Rappsilber_JP_CPC_phospho_EDC_R1.mgf"}, {"accession": "MS:1002846", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/Zou_Rappsilber_JP_CPC_phospho_EDC_R1.raw"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/Zou_Rappsilber_JP_CPC_phospho_EDC_R2.mgf"}, {"accession": "MS:1002846", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/Zou_Rappsilber_JP_CPC_phospho_EDC_R2.raw"}, {"accession": "MS:1002850", "name": "Peak list file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/Zou_Rappsilber_JP_CPC_phospho_EDC_R3.mgf"}, {"accession": "MS:1002846", "name": "Associated raw file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/Zou_Rappsilber_JP_CPC_phospho_EDC_R3.raw"}, {"accession": "MS:1002845", "name": "Associated file URI", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882/CPC_Nucleosomes.fasta"}], "description": "CPC-NCP complexes were crosslinked using EDC and analysed by mass spectrometry. The results showed Borealin is critical for nucleosome binding made extensive contacts with NCPs, whereas Survivin interactions are mostly limited to the BIR domain and the H3 N-terminal tail as expected. Mapping the crosslinks onto the three dimensional structures of NCP and CPC suggests a model where the localisation module of the CPC together with a highly basic N-terminal tail of Borealin docks onto the acidic patch formed by H2A and H2B, a surface commonly involved in nucleosome recognition. This interaction may orient the Survivin BIR domain to facilitate binding of histone H3 tail phosphorylated at Thr3. Notably, Borealin loop residues trace along the DNA-histone interface implying its major contribution to nucleosome binding involves both protein-histone and possibly protein-DNA contacts.", "fullDatasetLinks": [{"accession": "MS:1002852", "name": "Dataset FTP location", "value": "ftp://ftp.pride.ebi.ac.uk/pride/data/archive/2019/09/PXD012882"}, {"accession": "MS:1001930", "name": "PRIDE project URI", "value": "http://www.ebi.ac.uk/pride/archive/projects/PXD012882"}], "identifiers": [{"accession": "MS:1001919", "name": "ProteomeXchange accession number", "value": "PXD012882"}, {"accession": "MS:1001921", "name": "ProteomeXchange accession number version number", "value": "2"}], "instruments": [{"accession": "MS:1002732", "name": "Orbitrap Fusion Lumos"}], "keywords": [{"accession": "MS:1001925", "name": "submitter keyword", "value": "Chromosomal Passenger Complex, Nucleosome core particles, Crosslinking"}, {"accession": "MS:1001926", "name": "curator keyword", "value": "Biological"}], "modifications": [{"accession": "MOD:00696", "name": "phosphorylated residue"}], "publications": [{"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1000879", "name": "PubMed identifier", "value": "31570499"}, {"accession": "MS:1002866", "name": "Reference", "value": "Abad MA, Ruppert JG, Buzuk L, Wear M, Zou J, Webb KM, Kelly DA, Voigt P, Rappsilber J, Earnshaw WC, Jeyaprakash AA. Borealin-nucleosome interaction secures chromosome association of the chromosomal passenger complex. J Cell Biol. 2019"}]}], "species": [{"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1001469", "name": "taxonomy: scientific name", "value": "Xenopus laevis (African clawed frog)"}, {"accession": "MS:1001467", "name": "taxonomy: NCBI TaxID", "value": "8355"}]}, {"terms": [{"accession": "MS:1001469", "name": "taxonomy: scientific name", "value": "Homo sapiens (Human)"}, {"accession": "MS:1001467", "name": "taxonomy: NCBI TaxID", "value": "9606"